sentences: Scharrer made her London début at the age of 16, and gave concerts regularly until June 1958, where she appeared for the last time, playing Mozart's Sonata for Two Pianos with Myra Hess.
She visited Sir Edward Elgar in 1918 and was promised the first performance of his piano concerto, then being sketched.
From as early as 1909 she recorded for HMV, then between 1929 and the mid-1930s for Columbia.
